body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting us today. My name is Jordan Martin and I'm with CarzRUs. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Gloria. Could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five two three four one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. And could you also confirm your home address for us?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my address is one zero zero Elm Street, Citysville.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Gloria. We appreciate your cooperation with providing the necessary information. Is there anything else you would like to share with us?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I have some concerns about the pricing on your website. It seems a bit confusing.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your confusion, Gloria. We will look into this matter for you. Thank you for bringing it to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Gloria. Have a wonderful day.
